1 (f) the artificial intelligence, algorithm, or other software tool is fairly and equitably applied,
2 including in accordance with any applicable regulations and guidance issued by the federal department of
3 health and human services;
4 (g) the artificial intelligence, algorithm, or other software tool is open to inspection for audit or
5 compliance reviews by the department pursuant to applicable state and federal law;
6 (h) disclosures pertaining to the use and oversight of the artificial intelligence, algorithm, or other
7 software tool are contained in the written policies and procedures, as required by this section;
8 (i) the artificial intelligence, algorithm, or other software tool's performance, use, and outcomes
9 are periodically reviewed and revised to maximize accuracy and reliability;
10 (j) patient data is not used beyond its intended and stated purpose, consistent with the federal
11 Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act of 1996, Public Law 104-191, and this title, as applicable;
12 and
13 (k) the artificial intelligence, algorithm, or other software tool does not directly or indirectly cause
14 harm to the enrollee.
15 (2) Notwithstanding subsection (1), the artificial intelligence, algorithm, or other software tool may
16 not deny, delay, or modify health care services based, in whole or in part, on medical necessity. A
17 determination of medical necessity must be made only by a licensed physician or a licensed health care
18 professional competent to evaluate the specific clinical issues involved in the health care services requested by
19 the provider, as provided in subsection (1)(a)(ii), by reviewing and considering the requesting provider's
20 recommendation, the enrollee's medical or other clinical history, as applicable, and individual clinical
21 circumstances.
22 (3) This section applies to utilization review or utilization management functions that prospectively,
23 retrospectively, or concurrently review requests for covered health care services.
24 (4) A health insurance issuer subject to this section shall comply with applicable federal rules and
25 guidance issued by the federal department of health and human services regarding the use of artificial
26 intelligence, an algorithm, or other software tools. The department in consultation with the Montana department
27 of public health and human services may issue guidance to implement this section within 1 year of the adoption
28 of federal rules or the issuance of guidance by the federal department of health and human services regarding
